1.00	Amaru_(poet)	Amaru Shataka	The Amaruśataka or Amarukaśataka (अमरुशतक, "the hundred stanzas of Amaru"), authored by Amaru (also Amaruka), is a collection of poems dated to about the 7th or 8th century.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Amaru_Shataka_by_Amaru%2C_early_17th_century.jpg/220px-Amaru_Shataka_by_Amaru%2C_early_17th_century.jpg
